Phase 5 speech-evaluation corpus — third-party attribution

This project's speech-evaluation harness downloads (at CI time, into ephemeral
private runner storage — never committed to this repository) clips from the
following permissively-licensed corpora. Attribution is required by their
licenses and reproduced here.

1. LibriSpeech ASR corpus (subset: dev-clean, OpenSLR SLR12)
   License: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
   Source:  https://www.openslr.org/12
   Cite:    V. Panayotov, G. Chen, D. Povey and S. Khudanpur,
            "Librispeech: An ASR corpus based on public domain audio books,"
            ICASSP 2015.

2. AMI Meeting Corpus
   License: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
   Source:  https://groups.inf.ed.ac.uk/ami/corpus/
            (ASR-prepared distribution: https://huggingface.co/datasets/edinburghcstr/ami)
   Cite:    J. Carletta et al., "The AMI Meeting Corpus: A Pre-announcement,"
            MLMI 2005.

The CI job re-verifies each corpus's license and records the resolved dataset
version + per-artifact SHA-256 into the run report before use. Both licenses
permit redistribution and automated/commercial use with attribution.
